  [info] Manual `find`
   ╭─[test.lis:4:11]
 3 │   let xs = [1, 2, 3, 4]
 4 │   let _ = xs.filter(|x| x > 2).get(0)
   ·           ─────────────┬─────────────
   ·                        ╰── can use `find`
 5 │ }
   ╰────
  help: `filter(...).get(0)` builds the whole filtered slice. Use `xs.find(|x| x > 2)` to return the first match directly · code: [lint.manual_find]
